    "body": "## Summary\n- Remove explicit `warmup` and `rep` parameters from `do_bench` function calls across multiple example files\n- Use default values instead of hardcoded `warmup=10, rep=100` or `warmup=500, rep=10000`\n- Update regression performance test parameters to use larger default input sizes (M=N=K=4096, heads=32)\n\n## Test plan\n- [ ] Run regression tests to verify benchmark functionality works correctly with default parameters\n- [ ] Verify that performance measurements are consistent\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)\n\n<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\n\n## Summary by CodeRabbit\n\n* **Chores**\n  * Standardized benchmarking configurations across example files by removing explicit warmup and repetition parameters, allowing profilers to use default values.\n  * Increased default matrix sizes in GEMM and dequantization examples from 256–1024 to 4096.\n  * Updated attention example default parameters: head count changed from 1 to 32 in multi-head attention benchmarks.\n\n<sub>✏️ Tip: You can customize this high-level summary in your review settings.</sub>\n\n<!-- end of auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->",
